cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the development of a control strategy for reducing nitrite concentrations during wastewater treatment, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses a mathematical model (SimBio) to simulate the functioning of biofiltration units, which is a computational engineering approach.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The "commande sans modele" (model-free control) approach mentioned in the paper involves using measured nitrite concentrations to make corrections to the methanol injection rate, which could be considered a form of AI-based control.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions the development of new measurement and control loops for the wastewater treatment process, which could involve software engineering techniques.
- cs.DB (Databases): Although not a major focus of the paper, the development of new measurement and control loops could involve the use of databases for storing and analyzing data.
